Description: Windows-style single-seat RDP takeover for Linux (Plasma 6 Wayland)
 ConsoleRDP orchestrates KDE's krdpserver so that a Linux workstation
 behaves like a Windows box with Remote Desktop enabled: one desktop,
 one session, and whoever authenticates last (locally or via mstsc)
 takes the seat.
 .
 The orchestrator (consolerdp-daemon) watches the krdp journal, the
 systemd-logind session list, and the TCP/3389 socket to drive VT
 switching, xinput lockout, panel claim-screen, session lock and auto-
 unlock as an RDP session rises and falls.
 .
 This package ships the orchestrator, helper scripts, systemd units
 and config templates. The matching patched krdp and kpipewire
 libraries must come from the same release bundle; stock Ubuntu
 builds of those libraries will NOT work.
